 say that something is the case in spite of what has just been stated or whatever the circumstances may be.\nPeace could come only gradually, in carefully measured steps. Even then, it sounds almost impossible to achieve...\nShe was at her prettiest in her late teens, but even then she always had somebody who was prettier.\nB\nADJECTIVE USES', '尽管那样;即使那样\n和平只会逐渐到来，而且每一步都走得小心翼翼。即使那样，要实现和平听起来仍几乎不可能。\n她在十八九岁的时候最漂亮，但是即使在那时，也总有人比她更漂亮。\n形容词用法'], ["ADJ-GRADED\nAn even measurement or rate stays at about the same level.\nHow important is it to have an even temperature when you're working?...\nThe brick-built property keeps the temperature at an even level throughout the year.", '不变的;恒定的\n工作时周围环境温度恒定有多么重要呢？\n那栋砖砌的房子里全年温度恒定。'], ['ADJ-GRADED\nAn even surface is smooth and flat.\nThe tables are fitted with a glass top to provide an even surface.', '平坦的;光滑的\n桌子装了玻璃表面，因此十分平滑。'], ['ADJ-GRADED\nIf there is an even distribution or division of something, each person, group, or area involved has an equal amount.\nMany are tired of being unpopular because of their wealth and would encourage more even distribution of it.', '平均的;均等的\nDivide the dough into 12 even pieces and shape each piece into a ball...\n将面团分成12等份，每份揉成球状。\n很多人厌倦了因为自己的财富而不受欢迎，从而会鼓励更加均匀地分配财富。'], ['ADJ-GRADED\nAn even contest or competition is equally balanced between the two sides who are taking part.\nIt was an even game.\n...an even match between eight nations.', '（比赛、竞争等）平衡的，不相上下的，势均力敌的\n这是一场势均力敌的比赛。\n8个国家间一场不相上下的竞赛'], ["ADJ\nIf you are even with someone, you do not owe them anything, such as money or a favour.\nYou don't owe me. I don't owe you. We're even.", '扯平的;互不相欠的\n你不欠我，我也不欠你，我们扯平了。'], ['ADJ-GRADED\nIf your voice is even, you are speaking in a very controlled way which makes it difficult for people to tell what your feelings are.\nMy voice surprised me; it was even and emotionless.', '心平气和的;平静的\n我的声音听起来心平气和、不露一丝感情，这让我自己颇感惊讶。'], ['ADJ\nAn even number can be divided exactly by the number two.', '偶数的;双数的'], ['ADJ-GRADED\nIf there is an even chance that something will happen, it is no more likely that it will happen than it will not happen.\nThey have a more than even chance of winning the next election...', '（成败机会）各半的，对半的，相等的\n他们赢得下届选举的机会在五成以上。'], ['PHRASE\nWhen a company or a persn running a business breaks even, they make neither a profit nor a loss.\nThe airline hopes to break even next year and return to profit the following year...\nThe theatre needs to fill over ninety per cent of its seats every night just to break even.', '收支相抵；不赔不赚\n那家航空公司希望明年实现收支相抵，在随后一年重新盈利。\n那家剧院每天晚上需要有90%以上的上座率才刚刚能够收支相抵。'], ["PHRASE\nIf you say that you are going to get even with someone, you mean that you are going to cause them the same amount of harm or annoyance as they have caused you.\nI'm going to get even with you for this...\nDon't get angry, get even.\nC\nPHRASAL VERB USES\neven up", '跟…算账;与…扯平；向…报复\n我会跟你算这笔账的。\n与其生闷气，不如出口气。\n短语动词用法\n相关词组\neven out\xa0\xa0\xa0']]}]